---
source: crates/franken-node/tests/cli_subcommand_goldens.rs
---
Diagnose environment and policy setup

Usage: franken-node doctor [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  close-condition     Emit the dual-oracle close-condition receipt
  evidence-readiness  Report whether generated evidence is ready for operator trust
  workspace-pressure  Analyze workspace pressure and resource usage
  help                Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --config <CONFIG>
          Config file override (default discovery is used when omitted)
      --profile <PROFILE>
          Runtime profile override: strict, balanced, or legacy-risky. Controls security[PATH] behavior (not packaging profiles like local[PATH])
      --policy-activation-input <POLICY_ACTIVATION_INPUT>
          Path to policy activation input JSON for live guardrail diagnostics. Falls back to `FRANKEN_NODE_DOCTOR_POLICY_ACTIVATION_INPUT` when the flag is omitted; the CLI flag takes precedence (bd-lmbt0) [env: FRANKEN_NODE_DOCTOR_POLICY_ACTIVATION_INPUT=]
      --json
          Emit machine-readable JSON report
      --structured-logs-jsonl
          Emit structured diagnostic log events as JSONL to stderr
      --trace-id <TRACE_ID>
          Stable trace ID for correlating diagnostics [default: doctor-bootstrap]
      --verbose
          Show verbose diagnostic output
  -h, --help
          Print help
  -V, --version
          Print version
